Member States are annually requested to provide to UNESCO an update on the status of the judicial enquiries into these cases. On the basis of the information provided by Member States, the Director-General of UNESCO presents a biennial Report on the Safety of Journalists and the Danger of Impunity to the Intergovernmental Council of the International Programme for the Development of Communication (IPDC). Every other year, a chapter on the safety of journlaists is included in the World Trends in Freedom of Expression and Media Development Report.
